# To Start the app in development with nodemon and setting NODE_ENV to "production"
# Create a Run Configuration using a Runner: Shell, 
# Command should be: ./app-start-dev
# May need to give permision prior: chmod a+x app-start-dev-rem
# Environment Variables:
#   NODE_ENV - Type of deployment, "development" or "production" accepted
#   DOMAIN - Base domain for hosting domain. Ex:'https://localhost:3000'
#   MONGOLAB_URI - (Optional) A String to MongoLab database, If none supplied, uses local "mongodb://localhost/Loc8r"
#       Ex:'mongodb://jfbuser:jean4JN010116@ds023435.mlab.com:23435/heroku_nhfnbhd2'
NODE_ENV=development REMOTE=true DOMAIN="https://mean-project-jeanmfrancois1.c9users.io" nodemon